{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17623397","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17623397"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:10:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:10:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16859"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16859","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16859"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.12,0.02,0,0.86]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9549"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67374"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9549","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9549"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16859"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52826"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4911"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"9874"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22557"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22561"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67374","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67374"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe baroreceptor reflex is an important mechanism for maintaining cardiovascular homeostasis. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the immediate neural response to a drop in arterial blood pressure?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decreased output of both sympathetic and parasympathetic systems","Decreased sympathetic and increased parasympathetic output","No change in autonomic output until chemoreceptors are activated","Increased output of both sympathetic and parasympathetic systems","Increased sympathetic and decreased parasympathetic output"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWhen arterial blood pressure drops, reduced stretch of baroreceptors leads to \u003Cstrong\u003Eincreased sympathetic and decreased parasympathetic output\u003C/strong\u003E. This results in increased heart rate, cardiac contractility, and vasoconstriction resulting in an increased TPR to restore blood pressure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased sympathetic and increased parasympathetic output\u003C/strong\u003E - This would further lower blood pressure and worsen the situation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased output of both sympathetic and parasympathetic systems\u003C/strong\u003E - These systems have opposing effects and are not activated simultaneously\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased output of both sympathetic and parasympathetic systems\u003C/strong\u003E - This would not provide an appropriate compensatory response\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENo change in autonomic output until chemoreceptors are activated\u003C/strong\u003E - Baroreceptors respond immediately to pressure changes, before chemoreceptor activation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe baroreceptor reflex provides rapid blood pressure regulation through these autonomic adjustments, typically responding within seconds of detecting pressure changes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Baroreceptors in the carotid sinus and aortic arch detect changes in arterial blood pressure through vessel wall stretch.","When blood pressure drops, decreased baroreceptor firing leads to increased sympathetic and decreased parasympathetic output.","The baroreceptor reflex helps maintain stable blood pressure through autonomic adjustments to heart rate and vascular tone."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52826"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16859"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52826","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52826"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-05T09:26:00+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-05T09:26:32+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9549"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67374"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data